overview: The user initiated a project to enhance a Sleep Questionnaire
  application by adding database capabilities and an admin dashboard. The
  existing codebase already handled the questionnaire flow and PDF generation.
  The primary goal was to implement a database for storing questionnaire
  responses, enable CSV data export, and create a simple, password-protected
  admin interface. After clarifying the desired authentication complexity
  (simple password) and demographic data fields, a plan was developed. The
  implementation involved updating the data models and validation schemas,
  creating API routes for data persistence and retrieval, and building the admin
  dashboard UI. Initially, a custom session-based authentication was set up.
  However, following a user's suggestion for simplification, the authentication
  system was refactored to leverage Next.js middleware for route protection and
  a more straightforward cookie-based authentication, streamlining the overall
  security implementation. The chosen database was NeonDB (PostgreSQL),
  integrated via Prisma, aligning with the user's preference for a simple,
  serverless-friendly solution.
